data.description: This is a wonderful house on a cul-de-sac with access to major roads and commuting options.  The seller has meticulously maintained the home and you will see all the internal upgrades, but there are other features that are hidden from the eye but completed to make this home a “one-of-a-kind” option for you (see list in documents section of the listing).  The standard 3 bedrooms and 2 baths on a split level are here with a spacious living room with wood burning fireplace, and large separate dining room.  Both rooms have sand and stain in place hardwood floors that were recently redone.  The kitchen is open and has a nice breakfast area for your daily meals which includes a sliding door to the deck and flat, fenced back yard.  The owner’s bedroom has new carpet and 2 walk-in closets plus a beautifully appointed full bath.  The second bedroom is almost as large with a double closet; the third bedroom is nicely sized.  With all that, one of the things that sets this home apart is the room off the garage entry.  It can be either a family room or bedroom and has its own newly renovated full bath.  Your new home has new flooring, except for the living room and dining room where the hardwood floors have been refinished.  Additionally, it has been freshly painted.  The back yard is fenced with privacy fencing, is flat and has a nice deck and a separate fire pit.  The driveway and garage allow for plenty of parking with the garage door being less than a year old.  This is a gem that you don’t want to miss!  Seller has video/audio monitoring.
